q.p:
King Henry turns Papiſt and is abſolved by the Archbishop of Bourges in the Abby Church of S. Denis;


                        〈…〉
                     . againſt the ſaid Bishop the Pope is very angry for abſolveing the King, and till he obtaine it of the Pope, his Rebellious Roman Catholick ſubjects refuſe to obey him; Neither would the Pope be perſuaded to grant the King his abſolution, till his Majeſty had upon the matter totally ſuppreſſed the League.
